cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with storage systems and distributed storage systems in particular. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as availability codes are a type of erasure code, which is a topic in information theory. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses the queuing theoretical approach to analyze download time in storage systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the performance of storage systems and the analysis of system performance. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also relevant as the paper analyzes the download time in storage systems and discusses the performance of different types of codes.
